                <note rend="inline" type="source">574.D1/103: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-12T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 12, 1920—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>878. Your 1192, August 9th, 4 p.m.</p>
                <p>This Government concurs with British Government’s suggestion that Main Conference
                    be postponed and date of its convocation be determined by agreement at
                    Preliminary Conference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
